From edefc32ad8f9ddfa129b5ab34357730f31266df4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vince.ceccarelli@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 02:14:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(positioning): market-validated differentiation +
 /technology research page

Competitive positioning (grounded in category intelligence: US
service-model and EU rental-model ventures have validated robotic
painting at scale):
- Homepage: 'A validated market' section framing the wedge -- verified
  robotic painting: the deliverable includes the sensor-verified
  thickness record. Links to the full thesis.
- Business-model comparison (service vs rental vs verified RaaS)
  describes models, not named companies, with an explicit disclaimer --
  legally clean and evergreen.

New /technology page (PhD-level thesis, honestly labeled):
- Closed-loop coating verification: why mil-spec compliance matters,
  measured-while-applied control loop, thickness map as deliverable;
  status explicitly marked as 2026 pilot engineering target
- Scan -> Plan -> Verify autonomy: digital twin, coverage as
  constrained path optimization, as-applied record in the same model
- Coating performance data layer: the compounding dataset thesis +
  'customers own their job data' principle
- Hybrid crew model: robot takes volume spraying, skilled painters
  keep judgment work -- the economics every serious player has proven
- Active research agenda (labeled research, not features): RL
  spray-path adaptation under airflow disturbance, semantic job-site
  mapping, thickness-estimation sensor fusion, multi-robot coat
  scheduling; founding team's graduate research background (M.Sc.,
  RWTH Aachen) stated factually
- Pilot CTA: pressure-test the thesis, be named on the data

Wiring: Technology in primary nav, both footer columns, and the two
research-relevant feature cards deep-link to the thesis sections
